article.description: — Tyler Robertson scored 32 points as Portland beat Portland State 98-91 on Friday.
article.headline: Robertson's 32 lead Portland over Portland State 98-91
article.linkText: Robertson's 32 lead Portland over Portland State 98-91
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- — Tyler Robertson scored 32 points as Portland beat Portland State 98-91 on Friday. Robertson had six assists for the Pilots (3-0). Kristian Sjolund scored 16 points and Moses Wood had 15 points, while adding 11 rebounds. Cameron Parker finished with 23 points and six assists for the Vikings (0-1). Bobby Harvey added 14 points for Portland State. Isiah Kirby also recorded 14 points. Portland takes on Kent State on the road on Monday, and Portland State visits Seattle U on Sunday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
